Outlet component

To navigate between pages we can use <a href> tag, but this results in refresh of the whole page and that is expensive.
When using react we should try to use routing.
For this Link component from react-Router-dom is used.

Because of routing, in a website only components are reloaded not the whole page that's why these sites are called SPAs.

Types of Routing
i) Client side routing - when just the components are changing (using <Link/>)

ii) Server side routing - when the whole page is sent by server and loaded (using <a></a>)

